reviewText: This is a documentary about Seattle punk rock bar The Funhouse. The main subject of the film is Seattle DJ and bar owner Brian Foss, who bought into The Funhouse in 2006 and turned it into a venue for both new and established international punk bands. The film chronicles the Funhouse's full history from its early days as Tex's Tavern, to Zak's in the 1990s, and finally reaching its end in 2012 when it was demolished by developers to make way for apartments.
